1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
================================================================================

SupportEnv is a production-grade Reinforcement Learning (RL) environment that
simulates real-world customer support workflows. AI agents operating within this
environment learn to classify support tickets, respond to customers with empathy,
make escalation decisions, and resolve issues efficiently.

Customer support is a $400B+ industry where AI can deliver immediate, measurable
value. SupportEnv provides a standardised training and evaluation platform — built
on the OpenEnv specification — for developing, benchmarking, and comparing
autonomous support agents.

================================================================================
2. PROBLEM STATEMENT
================================================================================

2.1 Industry Pain Points
    - Customer support teams face high volume, repetitive queries, and agent
      burnout.
    - Existing AI solutions lack a standardised environment for training support
      agents end-to-end (classify → respond → escalate → resolve).
    - No open benchmark exists for comparing different autonomous support
      strategies under controlled conditions.

2.2 What SupportEnv Solves
    - Provides a deterministic, reproducible environment for RL agent training.
    - Offers progressive difficulty (easy / medium / hard) for curriculum
      learning.
    - Supplies deterministic grading so results are comparable across agents.
    - Exposes a WebSocket + REST API that any RL framework can consume.

