5. FEATURE REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

5.1 Core Environment Loop
    ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  reset(seed, difficulty)  →  Observation           │
    │  step(action)             →  Observation + Reward   │
    │  state                   →  Internal State          │
    │  grade_episode()         →  GradeResult             │
    └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

5.2 Action Space (Discrete, 5 actions)

    Action         Description                      Content
    ──────────     ────────────────────────────────  ─────────────────────
    classify       Categorise the ticket             billing / technical /
                                                     account / general
    respond        Send a response to customer       Free-text response
    escalate       Escalate to human agent           Reason for escalation
    request_info   Ask customer for more info        What info is needed
    resolve        Mark ticket as resolved            Resolution summary

5.3 Observation Space

    Field                   Type            Description
    ──────────────────────  ──────────────  ─────────────────────────────
    ticket_id               str             Unique ticket identifier
    ticket_text             str             Full ticket body
    ticket_subject          str             Ticket subject line
    customer_name           str             Customer's name
    interaction_history     List[Dict]      Chat history (role + content)
    customer_sentiment      float [-1, 1]   -1 = angry, 0 = neutral, 1 = happy
    current_classification  Optional[str]   Category if classified
    is_classified           bool            Whether ticket is classified
    is_escalated            bool            Whether ticket is escalated
    task_difficulty          str             easy / medium / hard
    steps_remaining         int             Steps left before timeout
    max_steps               int             Maximum allowed steps
    message                 str             Feedback message from env
    available_actions       List[str]       Actions currently valid

5.4 Reward Structure

    Event                              Reward
    ───────────────────────────────    ──────
    Correct classification              +0.25
    Good response (empathetic + fix)    +0.30
    Correct escalation decision         +0.35
    Successful resolution               +0.40
    Efficiency bonus                    +0.10
    Wrong classification                −0.15
    Harmful response                    −0.40
    Missed escalation                   −0.35

5.5 Task Definitions

    Task   Difficulty   Max Steps   Description
    ─────  ──────────   ─────────   ────────────────────────────────────────
    FAQ    Easy         5           Simple queries (password resets, hours)
    Multi  Medium       8           Billing disputes, technical bugs
    Esc    Hard         10          Angry customers, fraud, sensitive issues

    Expected action flows:
      Easy   : classify → respond → resolve
      Medium : classify → request_info → respond → resolve
      Hard   : classify → respond (de-escalate) → escalate

5.6 Grading System

    - Score range: 0.0 – 1.0
    - Deterministic: same episode data always produces the same score.
    - Dimension weights vary by difficulty:

      Dimension             Easy    Medium   Hard
      ────────────────────  ──────  ──────   ──────
      Classification        30%     25%      15%
      Response Quality      40%     30%      20%
      Escalation Decision    5%     10%      30%
      Resolution            15%     20%      20%
      Efficiency            10%     15%      15%

5.7 Baseline Agent
    - Rule-based policy shipped with the project.
    - Expected average score: 0.63
      ┌──────────┬───────┬────────┬───────┐
      │ Difficulty│ Score │ Reward │ Steps │
      ├──────────┼───────┼────────┼───────┤
      │ Easy      │ 0.85  │ 0.92   │ 3     │
      │ Medium    │ 0.65  │ 0.58   │ 5     │
      │ Hard      │ 0.40  │ 0.25   │ 4     │
      │ Average   │ 0.63  │ —      │ —     │
      └──────────┴───────┴────────┴───────┘

5.8 Web Interface (Gradio)
    - Mounted at /web.
    - Allows interactive ticket classification, response, and grading.
    - Useful for demos and manual exploration.

