7. API ENDPOINTS
================================================================================

Endpoint               Method   Description
─────────────────────  ──────   ─────────────────────────────────
/health                GET      Health check — returns 200
/tasks                 GET      List available tasks with schemas
/api/reset             POST     Start a new episode (HTTP)
/api/step              POST     Take an action (HTTP)
/api/state/{id}        GET      Get current internal state
/grader                POST     Grade a completed episode
/baseline              GET      Run baseline agent on all tasks
/web                   GET      Gradio interactive UI
/ws                    WS       WebSocket for real-time interaction

================================================================================
8. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

NFR-01  Performance   : Single episode (reset + 10 steps + grade) < 500 ms.
NFR-02  Concurrency   : Support ≥ 100 concurrent environments.
NFR-03  Reproducibility: Same seed + same actions = identical rewards & grades.
NFR-04  Portability    : Run on Python 3.10 / 3.11 / 3.12.
NFR-05  Security       : Optional API key, configurable CORS origins.
NFR-06  Logging        : Structured JSON logs, optional file output.
NFR-07  Rate Limiting  : Configurable (default: 100 req / 60 s window).

